&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost:4000/assets/images/age_points.png&quot; alt=&quot;season points by age&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="code" /><category term="R" /><category term="ggplot2" /><category term="tidyverse" /><category term="rvest" /><summary type="html">This is the first in a series of articles that will use historical data from NFL seasons between 1992 and 2016 to illustrate some data munging, analysis, and visualization techniques in R. Pro-Football-Reference.com has a wealth of freely available detailed historical data. We are going to use rvest and dplyr, part of the tidyverse, to scrape, clean, and concatenate that historical data.</summary></entry></feed>